# LLRE Integration Walkthrough

This document outlines the complete implementation, database integration, API routes, user interface updates, and test verification for the **Low-Level Reasoning Engine (LLRE)** integration into **PRISM**.

---

## Technical Architecture Overview

The integration introduces a formal TypeScript port of the LLRE capability matrix, seamlessly integrated into PRISM’s existing SQLite activity logging system. The components work in unison:

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Autonomous Planner] -->|Emits Event| B[Activity Bus]
    B -->|Listens & Intercepts| C[SQLite Activity Store]
    C -->|Saves Telemetry| D[(SQLite Database)]
    E[ApiHandler Gateway] -->|Queries Telemetry| C
    F[Front-End operator dashboard] -->|Fetches REST API| E
```

---

## Core Components Implemented

### 1. Mathematical Telemetry & Compiler Engine
- **AST Parser (`src/core/llre/ast.ts`)**: Delimits system and task prompts using `<objective>` and `<constraints>` XML envelopes, calculating token count and **Signal Density** (direct instructions vs descriptive padding text).
- **Telemetry Equations (`src/core/llre/telemetry.ts`)**:
  - **Tool Call Accuracy (TCA)**: $TCA = \frac{\text{Valid Invocations}}{\text{Attempted Invocations}}$
  - **Request Satisfaction Index (RSI)**: $RSI = \frac{\text{Passed Criteria}}{\text{Total Criteria}}$
  - **Context Saturation Ratio (CSR)**: $CSR = \min(1.0, \frac{500}{\text{Tokens Consumed}})$
  - **Token Efficacy Quotient (TEQ)**: $TEQ = \frac{RSI \times TCA}{\text{Cost USD} \times \text{Latency Seconds}}$

### 2. SQLite Database Persistence (`src/core/activity/sqlite-store.ts`)
- Configured a database migration to create the `prism_llre_telemetry` table.
- Added synchronous SQLite statements (`insertLlreStmt`) to serialize performance data.
- Handled asynchronous activity bus event interception to catch `llre.telemetry.recorded` events and write them durably in the background.

### 3. Planner Runtime Telemetry (`src/core/runtime/autonomous-planner.ts`)
- Measures goal planning cycles, tracking execution time, tokens used, and dollar cost.
- Triggers calculations via `LLRETelemetry.calculate` and publishes logs to the Activity Bus.

### 4. API Routing Gateway (`src/core/operator/routes/api-handler.ts`)
- Added `GET /api/llre/summary?sessionId=<id>` returning average cognitive metrics across a session's execution paths.

### 5. Premium Cognitive Economics UI (`tab-settings.html` and `tab-settings.js`)
- Added a high-end, responsive dashboard panel directly at the top of the Provider & Settings tab.
- Styled with modern glassmorphism, responsive CSS grid, live animated progress rings, glowing micro-animations, and dynamic metric bars.
- Integrated `refreshLlreTelemetry` to poll metrics periodically on session selections.

